1. Need to install Numpy :-
pip3 install numpy

2. When ever we want to use we need to import numpy in our code

3. Numpy is used to work with array, we can create 2-D, #-D Array also

4. numpy.array([arr_value1, arr_value2, arr_value3, arr_value4])

5. Array indexing, slicing, data types are used on Numpy Array

6. dimension of array:-
    1. arr_name.ndim,
    2. Slicing:- arr[0:4:2],
    3. To check the datatype :- arr_name.dtype
    4. Can change the data type of array :- arr_name.astype('i') # i stand for integer,
    5. Used to make new copy of array :- copy() and this is used to just view the original array :-  view()
    6. arr_name.shape() :- giver number of dimension and element inside each dimension